                  {
                    "markdown_text": {
                      "select_text_type": "body_copy_v2",
                      "select_semantics_type": null,
                      "markdown_text": "Barbie, which was founded by Ruth Handler in 1959, has evolved over the years. Here are some facts about the iconic doll from Barbiemedia.com. Find Barbie toys in Costco warehouses and at [Costco.ca](/.product.4000160795.html).\n\n - Barbie was named after Handler’s daughter, Barbara, and Ken, after her son, Kenneth.\n - The doll first appeared in her iconic black-and-white striped swimsuit.\n - The first celebrity Barbie doll was based on the British fashion model Twiggy in 1967.\n - In support of Equal Rights, Barbie released Christie, one of the first Black dolls, in 1968.\n - Barbie has had more than 200 careers, including astronaut, pilot, firefighter, journalist and entrepreneur.\n - More than 100 dolls are purchased every minute, with a total of 58 million sold annually in 150 countries.",
